<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="voice-n">voice <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /vɔɪs/    美 /vɔɪs/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>说话声；嗓音：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>in a low / loud voice</strong>
低/高声地</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I didn’t recognize her voice on the telephone.
在电话里我没有听出她的声音。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They were shouting <strong>at the top of their voices</strong>.
他们正在扯着嗓子大声喊叫。</p></div>

<h3 id="noise-sound-voice">辨析 noise, sound, voice</h3>
<p><strong>noise ** 通常指不悦耳的、令人烦恼的嘈杂声，隐含贬义。
</strong>sound ** 是普通用词，含义笼统，指人们能听到的各种声音，无褒贬色彩。
**voice ** 指人说话或唱歌时发出的声音。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>You’ll have to <strong>raise your voice</strong> if you want to be heard in here. 
在这里，如果想让别人听见你说话，你必须大点儿声。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I could hear angry voices in the next room. 
我能听到隔壁房间的怒吼声。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>意见；心声</strong></h4>
<p>a particular feeling, attitude or opinion that you have or express：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This programme gives ordinary viewers a chance to <strong>make</strong> their <strong>voice heard</strong> (= express their opinion sothat people notice it).
这个节目给了普通观众一个表达心声的机会。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Mary was silent during the early part of the discussion but finally she <strong>gave voice to</strong> her opinion on the subject.
在讨论的前期，玛丽很沉默，但最后她还是表达了对这个话题的看法。</p><footer>2016 天津</footer></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>语态：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the <strong>active / passive voice</strong>
主动/被动语态</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>To save some of the human languages before they are forgotten, the students in our school started a discussion “Save Our <strong><em>_</em></strong> ”.  （2008 安徽）<br />
A.Sky<br />
B.Life<br />
C.Arts<br />
D.Voices  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. D  </p></div>